Generate Dates for a 360-Day Year Calendar

Source: R/aux_functions.R
generate_360_day_dates.Rd

This function generates a sequence of dates assuming a 360-day year, with each month consisting of 30 days. Useful for simplified models where leap years and 31-day months are ignored.

Usage

generate_360_day_dates(start_year, end_year)

Arguments

start_year

The starting year of the date sequence.

end_year

The ending year of the date sequence.

Value

A vector of dates formatted as "YYYY-MM-DD" for each day within the given range, assuming a 360-day year.

Examples

generate_360_day_dates(2014, 2022)
